Protea is a striking and exotic flowering plant, often called the “King Protea.”

It is native to South Africa and is the national flower of the country.

Protea flowers are large, showy, and often have a spiky or layered appearance.

They come in colors like pink, red, white, and cream.

Protea plants are evergreen shrubs with tough, leathery leaves.

The flowers symbolize change, courage, and transformation.

Proteas thrive in well-drained, sandy soil with plenty of sunlight.

They are drought-tolerant and suited for warm climates.

Proteas are used in floral arrangements, landscaping, and ornamental gardening.

Their unique, long-lasting blooms make them popular worldwide in floristry.
